---
id: drowned_library
title: The Drowned Library
weight: 10
---

=== intro

The tide-bell has already rung twice. In an hour the sea reclaims the
Library of Vael for another century, and the Ledger of Tides — the only
record of who owns what along this whole drowned coast — goes with it,
unless your company carries it out tonight.

Torchlight. Three arches. The water is at your ankles and rising.

The company decides together. Choose.

* [Take the LANTERN from the warden's hook — the deep stacks are lightless]
  ~ lantern = 1
  -> arches

* [Leave the lantern; speed matters more than light]
  -> arches

=== arches

Three ways down. The bell tolls a third time somewhere above.

* [The Grand Stair — wide, obvious, and already half-flooded]
  -> stair

* [The Cipher Door — sealed with a lock of seven rings] { lantern >= 1 }
  ~ chose_cipher = 1
  -> cipher_door

* [The Drowned Cut — a flooded crawlway only the desperate use]
  -> cut

=== stair

You descend the Grand Stair into the reading-hall. Shelves rise into the
dark like the ribs of a whale. Somewhere ahead, the Ledger's iron case.

But the water here is chest-high and moving with intent.

* [Wade for the case — the Ledger is close] { lantern >= 1 }
  ~ have_ledger = 1
  -> hall_with_light

* [Wade for the case blind, feeling along the shelves]
  -> hall_dark

* [Retreat — the Cut, while there's time]
  -> cut

=== hall_dark

Blind, you misjudge the current. A shelf goes over; the case tumbles into
black water. You feel for it, and feel, and the cold climbs to your throat.

The company hauls each other back to the stair, empty-handed. Some things
the dark just keeps.

* [Climb out with your lives]
  -> ending_lost

=== hall_with_light

The lantern throws your shadows huge across the drowned hall. There: the
iron case, chained to a reading-desk. The Ledger is inside, dry.

The chain needs a key. Or a stubborn company and a pry-bar of driftwood.

* [Break the chain — loud, slow, but sure]
  ~ have_ledger = 1
  -> escape

* [You brought no key; improvise and go]
  ~ have_ledger = 1
  -> escape

=== cipher_door

By lantern-light the seven rings resolve into a riddle in the old coast-
script: a sequence of tides. Your company argues, aligns the rings, and
the door sighs inward onto a dry vault — the Keeper's own room, the Ledger
on a lectern, and beside it, the Keeper's Key.

* [Take the Ledger AND the Key — leave nothing]
  ~ have_ledger = 1
  ~ have_key = 1
  -> escape

* [Take only the Ledger; the Key is not yours to take]
  ~ have_ledger = 1
  -> escape

=== cut

The Drowned Cut is exactly as bad as its name. You go through it hand over
hand, lungs burning, and surface in a side-gallery — past the worst of the
flooding, but nowhere near the Ledger. You've bought speed and lost the prize.

* [Press on to the reading-hall from here] { lantern >= 1 }
  -> hall_with_light

* [Press on blind]
  -> hall_dark

=== escape

Ledger in its oilcloth, you run the rising dark for the tide-bell stair.
The sea is at your waists, then your chests. The last arch is a throat of
black water and you go through it together or not at all.

* [Go — all of you, at once, the Ledger held high]
  -> ending_saved

=== ending_saved

You break the surface under a sky going grey with dawn, the Ledger dry
above your heads, the Library gone under behind you for another hundred
years.

The coast will know, tomorrow and for every tomorrow, exactly who owns
what — because your company carried the record out of the dark, and no
tide, and no lord, can quietly rewrite what is written and witnessed.

A record saved is a truth the sea cannot take. THE END.

=== ending_lost

You make the shore alive but empty-handed. By noon the Library is fully
drowned, and with it the only witnessed record of the coast.

Within a year there are three claimants to every acre and no way to say
who is right — only who is loudest. What the sea took, the powerful will
invent.

Some things you only get to carry out of the dark once. THE END.
